          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "MOOC",
          "E-Learning",
          "Hybrid \n\n– Matrix Factorization: GMF, NeuMF\n\n– Collaborative: UserKNN, ItemKNN (cosine)",
          "Courses to Take",
          "43 021 learners",
          "24 321 courses",
          "– Course metadata (descriptions, categories)",
          "Each base algorithm as in the literature (e.g. random seed for Random; 100 neighbors for KNN; 10 latent factors for GMF/NeuMF)",
          "After base lists are generated, a fairness reranker adjusts ranks by optimizing a weighted equality–consistency objective controlled by λ",
          "– UTF‑8 lowercase tokenization of titles/descriptions\n– TF‑IDF vectors for content‑based\n– Ratings binarized for implicit CF\n– Graph‑based: P3‑α, RP3‑β with fixed α/β, k=200 neighbors\n– Hybrid: CoupledCF combining item+category embeddings\n– Negative sampling for MF",
          "Top‑10 ranked lists",
          "Global (λ = 0.01) metrics : • NDCG@10: Random 0.000, TopPopular 0.035, UserKNN 0.012, ItemKNN 0.021, P3‑α 0.001, RP3‑β 0.000, GMF 0.008, NeuMF 0.010, ItemKNNCB 0.042, CoupledCF 0.013 • Consistency: Random 0.586, TopPopular 0.516, UserKNN 0.618, ItemKNN 0.615, P3‑α 0.578, RP3‑β 0.572, GMF 0.662, NeuMF 0.652, ItemKNNCB 0.699, CoupledCF 0.717 • Equality: Random 0.872, TopPopular 0.795, UserKNN 0.885, ItemKNN 0.891, P3‑α 0.850, RP3‑β 0.847, GMF 0.917, NeuMF 0.906, ItemKNNCB 0.959, CoupledCF 0.969",
          "Introduces a fairness‑aware post‑processing layer on top of existing recommenders to balance accuracy with equality and consistency across learners in an online course platform.\n\nA model‑agnostic reranking framework that can wrap any base RS.A λ‑weighted objective combining two fairness metrics—Consistency and Equality—under three allocation strategies (Global, User‑proportional,Per‑learner). Demonstration that small accuracy sacrifices can yield large fairness gains.\n\nDataset & Split: COCO platform snapshot (6.56 M ratings; fixed‑timestamp split 2017‑06‑08; train ≥ 4 ratings/user; test ≥ 1).Base Algorithms (10): CF (UserKNN, ItemKNN), MF (GMF, NeuMF), graph (P3‑α, RP3‑β), content‑based (ItemKNNCB), hybrid (CoupledCF), plus random & popularity baselines.Reranking Strategies: Apply reranker post‑hoc under three λ allocation schemes, varying λ to trade off NDCG vs. fairness.Metrics: NDCG@10 for accuracy; Consistency & Equality for fairness.\n\nAccuracy (λ = 0.01): ItemKNNCB tops NDCG@10 at 0.042; CoupledCF at 0.013; baselines near 0.00–0.035.Fairness: CoupledCF achieves highest Consistency (0.717) and Equality (0.969); ItemKNNCB also strong (0.699/0.959).Trade‑offs: Under User‑ and Per‑learner strategies, modest NDCG drops (≤ 0.01) yield substantial fairness improvements (Δ ≥ 0.1).Key takeaway: A lightweight reranking step can substantially improve fairness with minimal impact on recommendation quality.",
          "– Equal max‑weight for all principles (no learner customization). – No live user evaluation; offline only. \n– Metrics ignore position‑sensitivity (top of list matters). \n– Only positive feedback modeled.\n– Reranker requires choosing λ—stakeholder decision with no guidance. \n– Fixed static split; no temporal/adaptive modeling of user changes. \n– Assumes consistency ≡ fairness—other fairness notions unexamined.\n – No assessment of computational cost or scalability for post‑processing at large scale."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
